          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-26 16:11:30" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to move nearer to a reference point</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to draw near</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to come near</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to approach</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages it is not possible to merely say ‘to come near,’ for it is necessary to specify the reference point, in other words, ‘near to what?’ One may accordingly translate this expression in {S:04201804000020} as ‘when he came near to Jesus, Jesus asked him.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
