          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-26 16:11:30" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the occurrence of a point of time close to a subsequent point of time</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to approach</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to come near</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to approximate</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though in many languages time may be expressed in terms of space, as in speaking of ‘time coming near,’ in other languages this may not be at all possible. Accordingly, this clause in {S:04002103400006} may need to be translated as ‘it was about time to harvest’ or ‘when it was about time to gather the grapes.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
